Fig. 12B
). Upper beak without well defined ridges or grooves. Lower beak with rounded hood, distinctly raised above crest; broad wings with distinct flexure running diagonally across; lateral walls without ridge or fold (
Fig. 12D
). Radula present (
Fig. 6E,F
), poorly developed, all teeth homodont. Anterior salivary glands small, attached to the base of the buccal mass; posterior salivary glands absent. Oesophagus twice the length of intestine. Stomach small, simple, appears as a swelling of the oesophagus. Caecum with single turn, connected to single-lobed digestive gland by two digestive ducts.

