Fig. 15B
). Upper beak lacking distinct ridges or grooves. Lower beak with rounded hood, slightly raised above crest; broad wings with distinct ridge running diagonally across; lateral walls without ridge or fold (
Fig. 15C
). Radula absent. Anterior salivary glands attached to the base of the buccal mass, posterior salivary glands absent. Oesophagus twice the length of the intestine; stomach small, a simple swelling of the distal oesophagus. Caecum with single turn, connected to single-lobed digestive gland by two digestive ducts.

